§ Results ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Given $a ∈ 𝗥$, define $f: 𝗥 → 𝗥$ by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f(x) = a^x \quad \text{for all } x ∈ 𝗥 ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ Then $f$ is differentiable and its derivative is the
    function $f': 𝗥 → 𝗥$ defined by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f'(x) = \ln(a)a^x \quad \text{for all } x ∈ 𝗥 ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>
¶ ⦊
  ‖ This proposition encompasses the special case $f(x) = e^x$
    then $f'(x) = e^x$. ⦉
⦉

